channel.title: Interleaved RSS Feed
channel.description: This is an interleaved feed of the most recent entries from each RSS source, skipping any feeds with errors.

item.title: Amazon CEO Andy Jassy: An ‘embarrassing’ amount of your success in your 20s depends on your attitude
item.description: But aspirational workers need to follow through on a can do attitude with action, Jessy added.

item.title: Britain expands AI safety institute to San Francisco amid scrutiny over regulatory shortcomings
item.description: The U.K. said Monday it will open a U.S. counterpart to its AI safety summit, a state-backed body testing advanced AI systems, in San Francisco this summer.

item.title: ‘No sign of life’ at crash site of helicopter carrying Iran’s president, others
Chinese state media hints that Beijing might ‘hit back’ against European probes by targeting wine, dairy and aircraft
item.description: The EU is investigating Chinese subsidies across a range of industries, threatening tariffs for electric carmakers and keeping firms out of rail and energy tenders.

item.title: Iran's President Raisi is dead. What does the leadership void mean for the country and the world?
item.description: All eyes are now on what comes next for the Middle Eastern power, which is home to nearly 90 million people and backs a number of regional proxy groups.

item.title: Stocks may rise into the summer. These 3 risks could derail the rally.
Gen Z fueling limited-time flavors like Sour Patch Kids Oreos and pink lemonade-flavored Kit Kats
item.description: Food companies are responding to the changing and expanding tastes of consumers while also trying to keep brands relevant and distinct to win space on crowded store shelves.

item.title: Monday's analyst calls: Micron gets an upgrade, hospital stock to rally more than 25%
item.description: A chipmaker was among Monday's biggest analyst calls along with a hospital stock.

item.title: What to watch as Nvidia, Target, Macy's and more report earnings this week
Utilities are doubling their 5-year electricity demand projections—but high interest rates and California's NEM 3.0 have U.S. solar in a holding pattern
item.description: Multiple macroeconomic and legislative challenges are slowing the growth of residential solar.

item.title: $9 billion travel tech firm Navan on track to hit profitability this year and 'not far' from IPO
item.description: The boss of travel and expense management platform Navan told CNBC he's preparing the company to get its business into shape for an IPO this year.

item.title: Why the Fed’s $7.3T balance sheet worries the world’s largest asset manager
Beijing is spending $42 billion to save its slumping real estate sector. Analysts say it’s nowhere near enough
item.description: The decline in China’s sales of new homes accelerated in recent months, with households increasingly preferring to buy in the secondary market.

item.title: Budget airline Ryanair posts record annual profit as passenger numbers soar
item.description: Dublin-based Ryanair said full-year profit after tax jumped 34% and announced a 700-million-euro share buyback program.
